          "vnum": 3116,
          "name": "Beneath a Treestump",
          "description": "You've crawled beneath a large, uprooted treestump within a clearing in the misted basin. The smaller roots dangle freely, covered in webs and various fungi. The pit contains the pungent, heady aroma of decay along with a faint stench of brimstone. A narrow tunnel leads through the earth to the west.",
